9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 1302, L.D. 1943, “Resolve, to Establish
10 a Commission to Study the Role of Private Equity in Maine's Economy and in Key
11 Economic Sectors”
12 Amend the resolve in section 1 in the indented paragraph in the first line (page 1, line
13 6 in L.D.) by striking out the following: ""private equity firm" means" and inserting the
14 following: '"private equity" means a class of investments or assets, including hedge funds,
15 venture capital, growth capital, mezzanine capital, leveraged buyouts, secondary buyouts
16 and carve-outs, used to purchase or invest in nonpublicly traded businesses or real estate.
17 For purposes of this resolve, "private equity firm" means'
18 Amend the resolve in section 2 in subsection 2 in the first line (page 1, line 13 in L.D.)
19 by striking out the following: "national,"
20 Amend the resolve in section 2 in subsection 3 in the first line (page 1, line 16 in L.D.)
21 by inserting after the following: "sectors" the following: 'in the State'
22 Amend the resolve in section 2 in subsection 3 in the 2nd line (page 1, line 17 in L.D.)
23 by inserting after the following: "energy," the following: 'child care,'
24 Amend the resolve by striking out all of sections 3 and 4 and inserting the following:
25 'Sec. 3. Membership. Resolved: That, notwithstanding Joint Rule 353, the
26 commission consists of the following members:
27 1. Two members of the Senate, appointed by the President of the Senate, including
28 one member of the party holding the largest number of seats in the Legislature and one
29 member of the party holding the 2nd largest number of seats in the Legislature;
30 2. Two members of the House of Representatives, appointed by the Speaker of the
31 House, including one member of the party holding the largest number of seats in the
32 Legislature and one member of the party holding the 2nd largest number of seats in the
33 Legislature;
34 3. One representative from the Department of Health and Human Services, appointed
35 by the Commissioner of Health and Human Services;
